_____________________________________________________________________________________

SWP - BELEG
Datenbankzugriff mit c++
_____________________________________________________________________________________

Installation Guide
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  Install the latest version of MYSQL ( dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/ )
    For further documentation visit: dev.mysql.com/doc 

    (If neccessary install the latest edition of make, doxygen and g++)

2.  Open the "fancyFunction.cpp" with your favorite editor.

3.  There add in the main function your username ("user"), password ("pass"),
    databasename ("database") and your tablename ("table"). 

4.  Save and close.

5.  In your downloaded folder enter the command: "make".

6.  Now everything should be ready to use.
_____________________________________________________________________________________

Configuration
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  If it is your first time using MYSQL or you want to create a new user for 
    interaction with the database, open the "config.sh" script with your favorite 
    editor.
 
2.  There add a name for your database, user, user password and list in the database.

3.  Save and Close.

4.  Execute the script. When asked for a password, use your root password, NOT the 
    password you just put in for the added user.
_____________________________________________________________________________________

How to use
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- To use the program enter the command "./beleg.x n1 n2 n3 n4..." where n1, n2,...
  are the parameters you give the program.

- Note that the parameters are read as double, so decimals and negative numbers are
  no problem. Also the number of parameters is not limited, the table of the database
  is just expanded to fit the given values. 
_____________________________________________________________________________________

Dokumentation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
After you entered "make" there will be a folder "html". In this folder
lies a index.html, the index page of the documentation.
